@PieterKas good suggestion, I will work on this. 

@arndt-s  My thinking: The issuing of identities must be coordinated so there are no conflicts.  Therefore it seems that it is best if the format is determined within the trust domain.  Issuers of identity credentials within the trust domain will generate identifiers for workloads, there may be more than one issuer so the format of the identifier.  The overall scheme is defined by the trust domain, portions of the name space can be delegated to specific issuers.
perhaps this is what you mean?
